item.title: Git cheat sheet
item.description: Git commands with specific keys ssh-agent bash -c 'ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_github; git clone git@gitRepoUrl' ssh-agent bash -c 'ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_github; git pull' ssh-agent bash -c 'ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_github; git push' Important things to know Private keys should have permission of 600 chmod 0600 ~/private_key Delete all merged branches git branch --merged | egrep -v "(^\*|master|develop)" | xargs git branch -d
